---
import PipeOp from "../PipeOp.astro";
---

<section class="grammar-teaser wrap">
  <h2>Five operators. That is the whole grammar.</h2>
  <dl class="ops">
    <div class="op-row">
      <dt><PipeOp kind="pipe" /></dt>
      <dd><strong>pipe.</strong> Pass the output of the left skill into the right.</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="op-row">
      <dt><PipeOp kind="repeat" /></dt>
      <dd><strong>repeat.</strong> Run the preceding stage N times, in parallel.</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="op-row">
      <dt><PipeOp kind="parallel" /></dt>
      <dd><strong>fanout.</strong> Run two stages concurrently; join their results.</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="op-row">
      <dt><PipeOp kind="conditional" /></dt>
      <dd><strong>conditional.</strong> Branch on a flag; either side is a sub-pipe.</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="op-row">
      <dt><PipeOp kind="sink" /></dt>
      <dd><strong>sink.</strong> Run for effect; discard the value.</dd>
    </div>
  </dl>
  <p>
    Read the full grammar in <a href="/grammar">Chapter 02</a>, including the
    production rules in EBNF.
  </p>
</section>

<style>
  .grammar-teaser { padding-top: var(--t-8); padding-bottom: var(--t-12); }
  .ops {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0;
    margin: var(--t-4) 0;
    max-width: var(--measure-wide);
  }
  .op-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 5ch 1fr;
    gap: var(--t-3);
    padding: var(--t-2) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    align-items: baseline;
  }
  .op-row dt { font-size: var(--step-2); margin: 0; font-family: var(--font-mono); }
  .op-row dd { margin: 0; }
  .op-row strong { font-weight: 600; }
</style>
